  "text": "Immunohistochemistry The labeled streptavidin biotin method was performed using a Histfine kit (Nichirei, Tokyo, Japan) for immunohistochemistry as previously described. 14 Briefly, cross-sections of hearts were incubated overnight with mouse monoclonal antibodies specific for 4-hydroxy-2-nonenal (4-HNE; Oxis, Foster City, CA, USA), which is a marker of oxidative stress. 20,29, [CITATION_1] The specimens were then incubated with biotinylated anti-mouse IgG. They were developed with FUJITA S et al.",
